# Wordle Clone

A terminal-based Wordle clone written in C++23.

## How to play

Guess the hidden 5-letter word in 6 attempts. After each guess the board updates
with color-coded feedback:

- Green  — correct letter, correct position
- Yellow — correct letter, wrong position
- Gray   — letter not in the word

A color-coded keyboard is shown below the board to track which letters you have
already used.

Guesses must be real words from the word list. The game ends when you guess
correctly or exhaust all 6 attempts.

## Build

Requires CMake 4.2+ and a C++23-capable compiler (GCC 13+ or Clang 16+).

    cmake -S . -B build
    cmake --build build

## Run

    ./build/wordleClone

## Project structure

    main.cpp      — game loop, input handling
    words.cpp/h   — word list loading and random word selection
    guess.cpp/h   — scoring logic and guess validation
    display.cpp/h — board and keyboard rendering (ANSI color codes)
    words.txt     — sorted list of valid 5-letter words
